"""Exact Japanese translations for the first half of The Englishire Standard."""

TRANSLATIONS = {
    "The Englishire Standard | Professional Teacher Cover": "Englishireの基準 | 専門的な講師代講",
    "A Published Statement of Practice": "公開する実務基準",
    "Principles for professional teacher cover in Japanese schools.": "日本の学校で専門的な講師代講を行うための原則。",
    "A school does not set aside its standards merely because a member of staff is absent. The Englishire Standard describes the care, judgement and professional conduct that should accompany every temporary teaching assignment.": "職員が欠勤したからといって、学校が教育水準を手放す必要はありません。Englishireの基準は、すべての短期の授業担当に必要な配慮、判断、職務上の行動を示します。",
    "Read the Standard": "基準を読む",
    "View Teacher Cover": "講師の代講・短期手配を見る",
    "First edition": "初版",
    "Preamble": "前文",
    "An absence may alter the timetable. It need not diminish the school day.": "欠勤によって時間割が変わっても、学校の一日の質まで下げる必要はありません。",
    "A teacher’s absence should never diminish a school’s commitment to learning.": "講師の欠勤によって、学校の学びへの責任が弱まってはなりません。",
    "Whether anticipated or unexpected, every absence presents a challenge which extends beyond the timetable. Lessons continue. Pupils continue. Expectations remain. Parents retain confidence that their children will experience a purposeful school day, and colleagues continue to rely upon one another to maintain the standards which define their community.": "予定されていた欠勤でも突然の欠勤でも、影響は時間割だけにとどまりません。授業は続き、生徒は登校し、学校への期待も残ります。保護者は子どもが目的のある一日を過ごせると信頼し、職員は学校を形づくる水準を守るために互いを支え続けます。",
    "Professional teacher cover exists to protect that continuity. Its purpose is not merely to place an adult in front of a classroom, nor simply to complete a vacant line on a schedule. It is to preserve, as far as circumstances allow, the quality, stability and confidence upon which effective schools depend.": "専門的な講師代講は、その継続性を守るためにあります。単に大人を教室に立たせたり、時間割の空欄を埋めたりすることが目的ではありません。状況が許す限り、学校運営に必要な教育の質、安定、信頼を維持することが目的です。",
    "This Standard sets out the principles which guide Englishire’s approach to temporary teacher cover in Japan. It is neither a catalogue of claims nor a promise that every circumstance can be made uncomplicated. It is a practical account of the judgement, preparation and conduct which should accompany responsible work in a school.": "この基準は、日本で短期の講師代講を行う際のEnglishireの指針を定めます。できることを並べた宣伝文でも、あらゆる状況を簡単に解決できるという約束でもありません。学校で責任ある業務を行うために必要な判断、準備、行動を実務的に説明するものです。",
    "Each school possesses its own character, routines and educational priorities. Those distinctions matter. Yet certain principles remain constant: careful preparation is preferable to hurried decisions; honest communication is preferable to unnecessary certainty; suitability should take precedence over convenience; and professional judgement should not be abandoned simply because time is short.": "学校ごとに、文化、日常の手順、教育上の優先事項は異なります。その違いは重要です。一方で、変わらない原則もあります。急いで決めるより丁寧に準備すること、不必要に断言するより正直に伝えること、利便性より適合性を優先すること、時間が短くても専門的な判断を放棄しないことです。",
    "Effective cover begins before a teacher enters the classroom. It begins with understanding the school, the pupils, the timetable, the expectations of leadership and the practical realities of the assignment. Every subsequent decision should strengthen that understanding rather than diminish it.": "有効な代講は、講師が教室に入る前から始まります。学校、生徒、時間割、責任者の期待、ご依頼の実務条件を理解することが出発点です。その後の判断は、その理解を弱めるのではなく、より確かなものにする必要があります。",
    "The objective is straightforward: to help schools preserve continuity, uphold educational standards and maintain confidence when circumstances require flexibility.": "目的は明確です。柔軟な対応が必要な状況でも、学校が授業の継続、教育水準、信頼を保てるよう支援することです。",
    "Contents": "目次",
    "Ten principles for dependable teacher cover.": "確実な講師代講のための10の原則。",
    "The Purpose of Teacher Cover": "講師代講の目的",
    "Every Assignment Deserves Proper Consideration": "すべてのご依頼を適切に検討する",
    "Suitability Before Availability": "空き状況より適合性を優先する",
    "Preparation Protects the Classroom": "事前準備が授業を守る",
    "Professional Conduct Without Fanfare": "目立つ演出ではなく、着実な専門性",
    "Continuity of Learning": "学習の継続",
    "Respect for the Character of the School": "学校の文化と方針を尊重する",
    "Clear Communication When Circumstances Change": "状況が変わったときは明確に連絡する",
    "Standards Which Cannot Be Compromised": "妥協できない基準",
    "Looking Beyond the Assignment": "一回のご依頼の先を考える",
    "Principle I": "原則I",
    "Teacher cover exists to protect the continuity of education, not merely to occupy a classroom.": "講師代講は、単に教室を埋めるためではなく、教育の継続を守るためにあります。",
    "The presence of an adult is not, by itself, a continuation of education. A lesson has purpose, sequence and an established place within a wider programme of study. Pupils arrive with expectations formed by the work which preceded it, and their next lesson will depend, at least in part, upon what takes place in the present one.": "大人が教室にいるだけでは、教育が継続しているとはいえません。授業には目的と順序があり、より大きな学習計画の中で位置づけられています。生徒は前の授業を踏まえた期待を持って登校し、次の授業も、少なくとも一部は今回の授業内容に左右されます。",
    "Temporary cover should therefore be understood as an educational responsibility rather than an administrative convenience. Supervision may be one element of that responsibility, particularly where circumstances allow little notice, but it should not become its entire definition. The aim remains to preserve meaningful learning wherever the available information, time and resources make that reasonably possible.": "したがって、短期の代講は、事務上の都合ではなく教育上の責任として捉える必要があります。急な欠勤では見守りが役割の一部になることもありますが、それだけを代講のすべてにしてはなりません。利用できる情報、時間、教材の範囲で合理的に可能な限り、意味のある学びを維持することが目的です。",
    "This requires attention to more than lesson content. Classroom routines, behaviour expectations, safeguarding arrangements, pastoral considerations and the confidence of pupils all form part of continuity. A capable temporary teacher recognises that the school day is an organised whole. One lesson cannot be treated as though it exists in isolation from the institution around it.": "必要なのは授業内容への配慮だけではありません。教室の日常手順、行動への期待、安全管理、学習者支援、生徒の安心感もすべて継続性の一部です。適切な短期講師は、学校の一日が組織された全体であると理解します。一つの授業だけを、学校全体から切り離して扱うことはできません。",
    "Continuity is proportionate, not theatrical": "継続性は、目立つ演出ではなく適切な対応に表れる",
    "Professional cover does not attempt to imitate the absent teacher, nor to introduce unnecessary novelty in order to make an impression. It seeks instead to preserve what matters: calm, purposeful work; appropriate expectations; and a clear handover which allows the permanent teacher or school team to continue without avoidable confusion.": "専門的な代講は、不在の講師を真似たり、印象を残すために不要な新しさを持ち込んだりしません。守るべきものは、落ち着いた目的ある授業、適切な期待水準、そして常勤講師や学校側が混乱なく続けられる明確な引き継ぎです。",
    "The measure of successful cover is seldom spectacle. More often, it is that pupils knew what was expected, learning proceeded in an orderly fashion, and the school remained confident in what had taken place.": "代講の成功は、目立つ成果で測られることはほとんどありません。生徒が求められていることを理解し、授業が秩序立って進み、学校が実施内容を信頼できたかどうかに表れます。",
    "Principle II": "原則II",
    "An assignment should not be accepted before its essential requirements are understood.": "重要な必要事項を把握する前に、ご依頼を引き受けるべきではありません。",
    "Urgency is a feature of many staffing enquiries. It is not a reason to dispense with judgement. Before an assignment is confirmed, there should be a proper understanding of the dates, location, timetable, pupil age groups, lesson expectations and any duties which extend beyond classroom teaching.": "講師手配のご相談には緊急性が伴うことがありますが、急ぎであることを理由に判断を省くことはありません。確定前に、日程、所在地、時間割、生徒の年齢層、授業内容、教室での指導以外の業務を確認します。",
    "The practical details matter because they shape the assignment. A day of primary provision differs materially from a secondary examination class. A familiar series of English lessons differs from a timetable divided across departments, campuses or age groups. Travel arrangements, arrival procedures and the time available between lessons may appear incidental, yet each can affect whether the work can be carried out properly.": "実務上の詳細は、ご依頼の性質を決めるため重要です。小学生を一日担当する場合と、中高生の試験対策授業では必要な経験が異なります。通常の英語授業と、部門、校舎、年齢層をまたぐ時間割も同じではありません。移動経路、到着手順、授業間の時間は小さな事項に見えても、業務を適切に実施できるかどうかに影響します。",
    "Consideration also protects the school from assurances which ought never to have been given. A hurried acceptance followed by revision, substitution or withdrawal creates more difficulty than a measured answer provided at the outset. It is therefore entirely proper to ask questions, clarify assumptions and, where necessary, decline an assignment which cannot be undertaken to a suitable standard.": "事前の検討は、後から変更や撤回が必要になる安易な確約から学校を守るためでもあります。最初に丁寧に確認して回答する方が、急いで引き受けた後に講師変更や辞退が生じるより負担を減らせます。必要な質問を行い、前提を明確にし、適切な水準で対応できないご依頼はお断りします。",
    "What should be understood before confirmation": "確定前に確認する事項",
    "The school location, reporting time and expected finish.": "学校所在地、到着時刻、終了予定時刻。",
    "The dates, frequency and likely duration of the requirement.": "必要な日程、頻度、想定期間。",
    "The year groups, class sizes and general learner profile.": "学年、クラス人数、学習者の概要。",
    "The subject content, materials and level of preparation available.": "授業内容、教材、事前に用意されている情報。",
    "Any form duties, break duties, clubs, meetings or pastoral responsibilities.": "担任業務、休憩時間の見守り、クラブ、会議、学習者支援などの付随業務。",
    "The school’s safeguarding, behaviour and communication procedures.": "学校の安全管理、行動指導、連絡手順。",
    "Not every detail will be available at first contact, particularly during an unexpected absence. The standard is not that schools must produce perfect information. It is that both parties should distinguish clearly between what is known, what remains to be confirmed and what cannot reasonably be promised.": "突然の欠勤では、最初のご連絡ですべての情報がそろわないこともあります。学校に完全な情報を求めるものではありません。ただし、確認済みの事項、未確認の事項、現時点では確約できない事項を双方が明確に区別する必要があります。",
    "Principle III": "原則III",
    "The fact that a teacher is available does not, by itself, make that teacher suitable.": "予定が空いているという理由だけで、その講師が適任とは限りません。",
    "Availability answers only one question. Schools require rather more. The teacher must be able to work with the relevant age group, understand the nature of the curriculum, conduct the classroom with confidence and adapt appropriately to the school’s established expectations.": "空き状況は判断材料の一つにすぎません。担当する年齢層への対応力、カリキュラムへの理解、授業運営の力、学校が築いてきた方針に適切に合わせられるかどうかも必要です。",
    "Suitability is not determined by a single credential or number of years in education. Experience is valuable, but its relevance must be considered. The calm judgement required in a junior classroom may differ from the subject confidence required in an upper-secondary lesson. Work with young learners, international programmes, examination preparation and adult education may all involve English teaching, yet they are not interchangeable.": "適合性は、一つの資格や教育経験年数だけでは決まりません。経験は重要ですが、その経験が今回のご依頼に関係するかを確認する必要があります。小学生の教室で求められる落ち着いた判断力と、高校生の授業で求められる教科への自信は異なります。子ども向け授業、国際プログラム、試験対策、成人教育はいずれも英語教育ですが、必要な経験や技能は同じではありません。",
    "Professional selection therefore concerns fit. It asks whether the teacher’s experience, disposition and practical abilities are appropriate for the particular assignment. It also asks whether the teacher can represent the school with discretion, follow instructions without unnecessary reinterpretation and recognise when a matter should be referred rather than resolved independently.": "講師の選定では、ご依頼との適合性を重視します。経験、気質、実務能力が授業に合っているか、学校を代表する立場として慎重に行動できるか、指示を不要に解釈し直さず従えるか、独自に解決せず担当者へ確認すべき場面を見極められるかを確認します。",
    "Suitability includes temperament": "適合性には人柄と落ち着きも含まれる",
    "Schools are communities as well as workplaces. A temporary teacher enters established relationships and routines. The ability to listen carefully, remain composed, accept guidance and exercise proportionate authority is therefore as important as confidence at the front of a room.": "学校は職場であると同時にコミュニティでもあります。短期講師は、すでに築かれた人間関係と日常の中に入ります。そのため、丁寧に話を聞くこと、落ち着きを保つこと、指示を受け入れること、必要な範囲で適切に指導することは、教室の前に立つ自信と同じくらい重要です。",
    "A suitable teacher need not arrive claiming to possess every answer. It is generally more reassuring to encounter someone who understands the limits of the brief, asks sensible questions and carries out the work entrusted to them with care.": "適切な講師とは、すべてを知っていると主張する人ではありません。依頼内容の範囲を理解し、必要な質問を行い、任された業務を丁寧に遂行できる人を重視します。",
    "Principle IV": "原則IV",
    "Professional teaching begins before the first pupil enters the room.": "専門的な指導は、最初の生徒が教室に入る前から始まります。",
    "Preparation is not an embellishment to temporary cover. It is one of the principal means by which uncertainty is reduced. A teacher who understands where to report, what is to be taught, which materials are available and whom to contact when a difficulty arises is better placed to begin the day calmly and to preserve that calm for pupils.": "準備は短期代講に添える飾りではなく、不確実性を減らす主要な手段です。到着先、教える内容、利用できる教材、問題が生じたときの連絡先を理解している講師は、落ち着いて一日を始め、その落ち着きを生徒にも保ちやすくなります。",
    "The briefing should be proportionate to the assignment. A single day may require concise but accurate information. A recurring or extended placement requires a fuller understanding of curriculum sequence, assessment, school systems, departmental expectations and the responsibilities which accompany membership of the wider staff team.": "事前説明の内容は、ご依頼の規模に合わせます。1日だけなら簡潔でも正確な情報が必要です。定期または長期の担当では、カリキュラムの流れ、評価、学校の制度、部門の期待、職員チームの一員として担う役割まで、より詳しく理解する必要があります。",
    "Preparation is shared work. The school provides the information and access reasonably available to it; the teacher reads what has been provided, seeks clarification where necessary and arrives ready to act upon it. Neither party benefits when important assumptions remain unspoken.": "準備は学校と講師の共同作業です。学校は合理的に用意できる情報とアクセス方法を提供し、講師は共有された内容を読み、必要な点を確認し、実行できる状態で到着します。重要な前提が言葉にされないままでは、どちらのためにもなりません。",
    "A sound briefing ordinarily addresses": "事前説明で確認する主な事項",
    "Arrival, reception, identification and the principal school contact.": "到着方法、受付、本人確認、学校側の主担当者。",
    "The timetable, rooms, transitions and arrangements for breaks.": "時間割、教室、校内移動、休憩時間の取扱い。",
    "Lesson plans, resources, technology and expected outcomes.": "授業計画、教材、使用機器、期待される学習成果。",
    "Behaviour routines, rewards, sanctions and referral procedures.": "行動指導の方針、評価・注意の方法、問題発生時の報告手順。",
    "Safeguarding information and any relevant pupil considerations.": "安全管理上の情報と、生徒に関する必要な配慮。",
    "What should be recorded or handed over at the close of the day.": "授業後に記録・引き継ぎすべき事項。",
    "Where full lesson plans are unavailable, the absence of detail should be stated plainly. A sensible alternative can then be agreed. Improvisation may occasionally be necessary, but it should arise from informed judgement rather than preventable neglect.": "詳細な授業計画がない場合は、そのことを明確に共有し、実施可能な代替案を事前に確認します。その場での調整が必要なことはありますが、避けられた準備不足を即興で補うことを前提にはしません。",
    "Principle V": "原則V",
    "Professionalism is most convincing when it is evident in ordinary conduct.": "専門性は、日々の落ち着いた行動に表れるときに最も信頼されます。",
    "Schools should not have to request the elementary courtesies of professional life. Punctuality, suitable presentation, attentive communication and respect for confidentiality are not exceptional achievements. They are the proper foundation of work undertaken in the presence of children and on behalf of an educational institution.": "時間厳守、適切な身だしなみ、丁寧な連絡、守秘義務は、学校が改めて求めるべき特別な成果ではありません。子どもたちの前で教育機関を代表して働くうえでの基本です。",
    "A temporary teacher occupies a position of trust from the moment an assignment is accepted. That trust extends to the way school information is handled, how colleagues are addressed, how pupils are spoken about and the discretion shown outside the classroom. Familiarity with a school may grow over time; professional boundaries should remain clear throughout.": "短期講師は、ご依頼を引き受けた時点から学校の信頼を預かります。学校情報の取扱い、同僚への接し方、生徒についての話し方、教室外での言動にも慎重さが必要です。同じ学校を継続して担当し、親しさが増しても、職務上の境界は常に明確に保ちます。",
    "Conduct also includes reliability in small matters. Messages should be acknowledged. Changes should be communicated promptly. Difficulties should not be concealed in the hope that they will pass unnoticed. A school should receive an accurate account of what occurred, expressed with judgement and without unnecessary drama.": "専門的な行動は、日々の小さな対応にも表れます。連絡には確実に応答し、変更は速やかに共有します。問題が気づかれずに済むことを期待して隠しません。学校には、事実を正確かつ落ち着いて報告します。",
    "Authority should remain proportionate": "必要な範囲で適切に指導する",
    "A temporary teacher is expected to lead the classroom, but not to recast the institution. Existing routines and policies should be followed unless safety or professional duty requires otherwise. When uncertain, the proper course is usually to seek guidance from the person appointed by the school.": "短期講師には授業を進める責任がありますが、学校の制度や方針を作り替える立場ではありません。安全上または職務上の理由がない限り、既存の手順と方針に従います。不明な点は、学校が指定した担当者に確認します。",
    "Quiet competence is preferable to conspicuous confidence. The purpose of the assignment is to support the school, not to make the temporary teacher its centre of attention.": "目立つ自信より、落ち着いた実務能力を重視します。ご依頼の目的は学校を支えることであり、短期講師を中心に据えることではありません。",
}
